    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen loading a file through `:edit` or such, it's possible to control what's done with the swap file using `SwapExists` and `v:swapchoice`. `bufload`'s current behavior is that `SwapExists` is ignored, an unavoidable error message is printed, and through `vim.fn` in Lua it seems that the buffer is loaded with read errors (the `x` indicator is shown in `:ls`).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n:lua vim.fn.bufload(vim.fn.bufadd(fname))\n```\nwhere `fname` is the name of a file with an existing swap file\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPerhaps the `SwapExists` autocmd could be triggered.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-726+ga69f2db773\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes. `vim.fn` issue not applicable.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If you want the swap dialog, you can do `:edit` (no args) after the load?\n\n> Perhaps the `SwapExists` autocmd could be triggered.\n\nthe current behavior is documented...\n\n    If there is an existing swap file for the file of the buffer,\n    there will be no dialog, the buffer will be loaded anyway.\n\nwhy should we change it?",
